HEADWORD: Oxindol
<hw>Ox*in"dol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ox</ets>ygen +
<ets>indol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
nitrogenous substance (<chform>C8H7NO</chform>) of the indol group,
obtained by the reduction of dioxindol. It is a so-called
<xex>lactam</xex> compound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

